bilingual.source: My teddy bear has got one ear!
bilingual.target: 我的泰迪熊只有一只耳朵！

bilingual.source: "I'm coming up there to pull you down by the ear."
bilingual.target: “我上去揪你耳朵把你拉下来。”

bilingual.source: She covered her ear with her hand.
He has a good ear for music.
bilingual.target: 他对音乐有很好的耳朵。
巨大的噪音伤害了我的耳朵。

list.abstract: 文件扩展名，全称是Enterprise Archive File，是指JAR生成的一个打包文件，通常是EJB打成ear包。 JAR（Java Archive，Java 归档文件）是与平台无关的文件格式，它允许将许多文件组合成一个压缩文件。为 J2EE 应用程序创建的 JAR 文件是 EAR 文件（企业 JAR 文件）。 EAR(Enterprise Archive file) 包含内容：Servlet、JSP页面、JSP标记库、JAR库文件、HTML/XML文档和其他公用资源文件，如图片、音频文件等； 除了包含JAR、WAR以外，还包括EJB组件· EAR包含4种模块：EJB; WEB; Resource Adapter;资源适配器 Client Application; 3类档案文件：WAR，RAR，JAR 用途：用于发布和使用类库，作为应用程序和扩展的构建单元 作为组件、applet 或者插件程序的部署单位，用于打包与组件相 关联的辅助资源。

yingyinNormal.en: Look at your ear. Let's get you cleaned up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瞧你的耳朵，我去帮你清理一下吧。

yingyinNormal.en: They don't hear it. Goes in one ear and out the other.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们才没听到，一个耳朵进，另一个耳朵就出了。

yingyinNormal.en: Do you really think your lips in my ear is helping?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你真以为对着我耳朵这么讲话有用吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Yesterday. You made me look in your ear to see if there was a ladybug in it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 昨天，你要我帮你看看你耳朵里是不是有瓢虫。

yingyinNormal.en: If you hold them to your ear, you can hear the sea. Yes, I can hear the seaside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 把贝壳放在耳朵上可以听见大海的声音。没错，我听见了大海的声音。

yingyinNormal.en: If you hold them to your ear, you can hear the sea. Yes, I can hear the seaside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 把贝壳放在耳朵上可以听见大海的声音。没错，我听见了大海的声音。

yingyinNormal.en: I have seen stocks of corn with better physiques. Makes you wanna pull an ear off, Private.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我看库存的玉米都有更好的体质。让你想扯掉哪只耳朵，列兵。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, and two years ago, you had a persistent ear infection. I hope that didn't cause any hearing loss.
yingyinNormal.zh: 两年前，你耳朵受持续性感染所苦，希望那没影响你的听力。

yingyinNormal.en: Don't be so hard on him. It's natural to be a little cranky when you have a quarter in your ear!
yingyinNormal.zh: 别对他这么凶嘛，他这么烦躁有情可原，因为他耳朵里有25美分！

yingyinNormal.en: Edmond, I think there's something behind your ear. Every one has found a chocolate egg.
yingyinNormal.zh: 啊，埃德蒙，我觉得你的耳朵后面好像有个东西。每个人都找到了巧克力彩蛋。

yingyinNormal.en: If you put a shell to your ear, you could hear the sea. I can hear the sea. I love my seashell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你把海螺放在耳朵旁边，就可以听到海了。我听到海的声音了！我好喜欢这个海螺。

yingyinNormal.en: My justice is divine. My laws are so simple you could write them on a pig's ear. In fact, I have.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我就是最高法律，我的法律很简单，简单到可以写到猪耳朵上，我也的确写上去了。

yingyinNormal.en: It is not my leg that is itching. It is my ear. Is it better? Yes, thank you. Lunch time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实不是我的腿感觉有点痒，而是我的耳朵感觉有点痒。这样好些了吗？是的，谢谢你。午餐时间到！

yingyinNormal.en: Just last week, you took her to the doctor without even asking! 'Cause she had an ear infection! Let's say we're even.
yingyinNormal.zh: 就在上周，你带她去看医生，连问都没问我！因为她耳朵感染了！算我们扯平了！

yingyinNormal.en: Nothing changes. You painted a cat. The cat's on a bench! I don't see the bench. I will cut my ear off right now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我画的就是啊。你画的是只猫。是长椅上的猫。我没看见长椅。我马上把我的耳朵割下来。

yingyinNormal.en: Doctor Brown Bear has come to see how Pedro is doing. How are we, today, Pedro? My ear is a bit itchy. Just here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 棕熊医生过来看看佩德罗的情况。今天感觉怎么样，佩德罗？我的耳朵感觉有点痒，就是这儿。

yingyinNormal.en: There was this great Polish guy, wire walker, Roman. He said he could tell when cable was at correct tension through his ass and through his ear. Ah!
yingyinNormal.zh: 有一个厉害的波兰走钢索人，罗曼，他说他能靠臀部和耳朵判断钢索是否拉得够紧。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah, but he did have to have a bunch of stitches and he said that only once in a blue moon does a dog's ear grow back, so still hoping.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可是他必须帮它缝好多针，而且他还说只有出现蓝月亮时狗才会再长出耳朵来的，所以还有一点点希望。

yingyinNormal.en: When is the last time I asked you to do something that wasn't a medical emergency? Yesterday. You made me look in your ear to see if there was a ladybug in it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我上一次叫你帮我做非紧急医疗的事是什么时候？昨天，你要我帮你看看你耳朵里是不是有瓢虫。

yingyinNormal.en: Here's my offer. Your board of directors, you got them in the other ear? Why don't you tell them this. If they dump you, I'll consider it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的提议如下。你的董事会成员，从另一只耳朵里能听到吗？不如你告诉他们。如果他们炒了你，我就考虑加入。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Their reactions may be a complex combination of instant reflexes, and what their eyes and <highlight>ears</highlight> tell them in that moment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们的反应可能是瞬间反射和他们的眼睛和耳朵在那一刻告诉他们的复杂组合。

examination_example.sentence: But there are nerves (神经) running through the middle <highlight>ear</highlight> that connect the tongue (舌头) to the brain.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是有神经穿过中耳连接舌头和大脑。

examination_example.sentence: A small fly came, flying and buzzing near his <highlight>ear</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一只小苍蝇飞来，在他耳边飞来飞去，嗡嗡作响。

examination_example.sentence: If your throat tickles (发痒), pressing your <highlight>ear</highlight> might make it go away.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你的喉咙发痒，按耳朵可能会让它不了了之。
